Sri Lankan Sailors Confined for Arson
COLOMBO , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- Ten sailors who were involved in the clash between soldiers and civilians in southern Sri Lanka last Thursday have been confined , according to naval sources here Monday .
Thirty other sailors will also be dealt with very soon , the sources said .
Eighty-five houses were damaged and 11 personnel were injured following the clash between the villagers and sailors at Pitiwella , 70 km from Colombo in the Southern Province .
Commodore Weerasekara said that he takes full responsibility for the arson and personally apologized to the villagers at a meeting held recently in Galle , the sources added .
